    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="986"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d986">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1"
                    >EW</gloss>/7–2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 986<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">and the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_CWL1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clayton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d986fn1">Sent over the signature of <persName
                            corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21">July 21,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss>–184. From <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CWL1">Clayton</persName>.</p>
                <p>In view of note presented by <gloss target="#t_AmEmbassy1">AmEmbassy</gloss>
                    Moscow to Soviet [Government]<note n="2" xml:id="d986fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d985">documents Nos. 985</ref> and <ref target="#d997"
                            >997</ref>.</note> based on your July 18 [<hi rend="italic">17</hi>]
                    telegraphed instructions re Spanish situation,<note n="3" xml:id="d986fn3">
                        <ref target="#d982">Document No. 982</ref>.</note> believe it highly
                    desirable to repeat to Moscow your telegram 56, July 18, re Rumanian oil
                        shares.<note n="4" xml:id="d986fn4">
                        <ref target="#d984">Document No. 984</ref>.</note> Also believe desirable to
                    repeat to Moscow details of Soviet negotiations re German property in Stockholm,
                    both in case of Soviet questions on note presented by Embassy. See no reason not
                    to repeat telegram re Rumanian oil shares to Bucharest.</p>
                <p>American delegation is presenting to conference its view that a declaration
                    should be issued by US, <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>, USSR, and if possible
                    France, declaring German external assets subject to jurisdiction of powers
                    occupying Germany and of <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss>, and naming
                    diplomatic representatives of occupying powers as agents for both.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d986fn5">For the text of the proposal presented by the United States
                        Delegation on July 30, see <ref target="#d1000">document No.
                        1000</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RSJ1">Rubin</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DJEJ1"
                        >Dubois</persName> here working on text of proposed vesting decree with view
                    to presenting decree to US Group <gloss target="#t_CC1">CC</gloss> for
                    presentation to <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss>.<note n="6" xml:id="d986fn6"
                        >See the attachment to <ref target="#d1003">document No. 1003</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_ES1">ES</gloss> comments being considered.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
